<script type="text/javascript">
function dothecalc() {
	var thewordcount = document.getElementById("wordcount");

	document.getElementById('act1').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.25);
		document.getElementById('hero1').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.05);
			document.getElementById('tot1').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero1').value)
		document.getElementById('hero2').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.05);
			document.getElementById('tot2').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero2').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot1').value)
		document.getElementById('hero3').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.05);
			document.getElementById('tot3').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero3').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot2').value)
		document.getElementById('hero4').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.05);
			document.getElementById('tot4').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero4').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot3').value)
		document.getElementById('hero5').value=Math.round(act1.value-(Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.05)*4));
			document.getElementById('tot5').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero5').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot4').value)
	document.getElementById('act2').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.5);
		document.getElementById('hero6').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.125);
			document.getElementById('tot6').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero6').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot5').value)
		document.getElementById('hero7').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.125);
			document.getElementById('tot7').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero7').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot6').value)
		document.getElementById('hero8').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.125);
			document.getElementById('tot8').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero8').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot7').value)
		document.getElementById('hero9').value=Math.round(act2.value-(Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.125)*3));
			document.getElementById('tot9').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero9').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot8').value)
	document.getElementById('act3').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.25);
		document.getElementById('hero10').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.0833333333);
			document.getElementById('tot10').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero10').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot9').value)
		document.getElementById('hero11').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value*0.0833333333);
			document.getElementById('tot11').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero11').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot10').value)
		document.getElementById('hero12').value=Math.round(thewordcount.value-document.getElementById('tot11').value);
			document.getElementById('tot12').value=Number(document.getElementById('hero12').value)+Number(document.getElementById('tot11').value)
}
</script>

<p>
Enter your word count goal (no commas, periods, etc) for your story below and then hit the "Calculate" button.
You'll be presented with word count goals based on the standard Three Act Structure
combined with the Twelve Step Hero's Journey. The "Section Count" column shows how many
words (approximately) that step in the Hero's Journey should be in order to keep on 
track towards your word count goal within the normal 25%/50%/25% structure of the standard
Three Act Structure. The "Running Total" column shows approxiumately how many words you should
have total in your story by the time you finish writing that step of the Hero's Journey
You can use this table as a sort of ruler or guideline to make sure
you're creating a cohesive story that doesn't drag on too long in spots or that does not devote
enough attention to areas that it should. I hope this helps with your stories. Remember though,
this is only a guide and you should feel free to deviate from the line!
</p>

